          "email": "talasila@research.att.com",
          "username": "talasila"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-11-27 20:20:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nHi Jess, I did mention to LF team in email not to branch \"portal\" or \"portal/sdk\" repos. I see that \"portal\" repo is not branched for Amsterdam as part of this branching effort by LF, which is good. However, \"portal/sdk\" repo is branched, which we do not want. As 1.3.2 points to same sha1, it should be OK. To be consistent, can you please remove amsterdam branch for \"portal/sdk\" or you want to create amsterdam branch for \"portal\" repo also with same sha1 as portal's \"release-1.3.0\" branch?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
